VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(?:eval|exec)\b
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:\$_(GET|POST|REQUEST|COOKIE)|base64_decode|gzinflate|str_rot13|preg_replace && MISSING:allowlist|whitelist
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects usage of eval() and exec(), which can lead to arbitrary code execution vulnerabilities.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Arbitrary Code Execution: eval and exec.
